Badger Sponsorship 2023 baby! 

My favorite initiative that we do at The Trek. We’ve partnered with some of the best names in backpacking who’ve donated more than $28,000 worth of gear to giveaway to YOU (assuming you’re US based and 18+).  

You buy raffle tickets, in a couple weeks we draw 15 names out of a gigantic virtual hat, the winners receive one of these absolutely bomber prize packages.  Every single penny that goes into the raffle goes directly to the @nationaltrailssystem , a non-profit dedicated to our wonderful national trails.  

The scientific term for this is a win-win-win.  You win, the national trails win, and therefore, WE ALL WIN.  Get all the deets through the link in my profile.  #winning #badgersponsorship2023 #badgersponsorship

In this week’s episode of Backpacker Radio presented by The Trek, we are chatting all things Pacific Crest Trail, round two. We are joined by our pal and two-time PCT thru-hiker, Michael “Grizzly” Ivey to talk through our top advice for hiking the PCT, with a special emphasis on doing so during a high snow year, which 2023 is shaping up to be. We go through suggestions for traveling through a snowy Sierra, including estimating food carries, how to approach water crossings, grouping, self-arresting skills, and more. We also chat through some more general tips including how to budget zero days, evaluating what type of hiker you are, and how to mentally approach the hike overall during a year with a large potential for chaos. We wrap the panel by breaking down how our gear changed from one section to the next during our own PCT hikes. #backpackerradio #thetrek #pct

This just in: Backpacking is good. 

I was gifted a few days away to explore the Washington backcountry with my longtime pal @ctopherpetersen. After a fire in the North Cascades derailed our original itinerary, we decided to to explore Goat Rocks Wilderness, a stretch of trail I’ve been dreaming of returning to since the PCT. It was every bit as magical as I had remembered. Got to walk down memory lane and explore some new areas around the Wilderness. 

It kicked a heroic dose amount ass and served as my requisite periodic reminder that the backcountry is in fact medicine for the soul. #thetrek
